Thats 23 tracks for a measly Â£2, including beauties from Fast Reaction, Panic! At The Disco, Fleeing From Finales, Promise of Redemption, oh and of course Paige!

description: Paige’s debut EP serves up five slices of refreshing pop-punk with lashings of keys and synth. You’ve Got Guts (Shame We’ve Gotta Clean ‘Em Up 4. Silhouettes 5. Actions

name: Friendly Fire - NOR001
description: No Order Records debut compilation Friendly Fire is a 50/50 split of some of the best UK and US bands about. Everything from international band of the moment Panic! At The Disco to unsigned UK acts like Fast Reaction is covered aswell as an exclusive Denver Harbor track to wrap things up. 1.Fastlane – Virus 2.Halifax - Ten Figures Isn’t Enough 3.Fleeing From Finales – An Emotional Summer Of Cricket 4.Park – Your Latest Victim 5.Chaser – I’ll Be On The Other Side (Riot) 6.Sherwood – The Town That You Live In 7.Kill The Arcade – This Is What We Call A Conflict 8.Panic! At The Disco – The Only Difference Between Martyrdom and Suicide Is Press Coverage 9.The Riverclub – Call If You Want To 10.The Prize Fight – This Apartment 11.Failsafe – Unity In Progress 12.Over It – Waiting 13.Fast Reaction – Out Of The Race 14.Promise Of Redemption – Carly 15.Loveburger – Before Today 16.Bottom Line – Nothing Is Real 17.The Attika State – The Downside Of Perfect 18.Denver Harbor – All I Want (Exclusive Acoustic Version)
